Title: Object: The Glory of Old England
Object: Briton's Protection
Description: Music cover (?) with a mock coat of arms showing Britannia in a roundel seated on the shore with ships at sea and an army camp behind her, a portrait of George III, "Whom God Preserve", on a medallion suspended below; a sailor and a soldier, holding a flag lettered "Egypt", as supporters, standing respectively on a lion and a unicorn, patriotic songs listed on a tablet between the animals; a crown as the crest; military trophies with flags of "Holland", "Spain" and "France" below; the names of commanders on ribbons at top and sides. 1 August 1803 Hand-coloured etching
Associated names: Portrait of: George III, King of the United Kingdom
